<subSubSection lastPageId="140" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="139.[151,1436,1685,1999]" box="[199,1384,1757,1783]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1757,1782]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Description.</emphasis>
Thinly encrusting on a dead oyster shell. Color in alcohol brown. Thickness less than 
<quantity box="[1312,1380,1758,1782]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[151,1436,1685,1999]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1794,1819]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Skeleton.</emphasis>
Hymedesmioid (
<figureCitation box="[503,587,1794,1819]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="140.[151,250,1473,1495]" captionTargetBox="[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@140.[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 87. Hymedesmia (Stylopus) alcoladoi sp. nov., holotype RMNH Por. 9956, a, SEM image of choanosomal skeleton, b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, large acanthostyle, b 1, detail of b, c, small acanthostyle, d, tornote, d 1, details of d." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273038/files/figure.png" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
a), with long acanthostyles and short acanthostyles erect on the substratum, heads embedded in a basal spongin plate. Choanosome and surface skeleton composed of scattered tornotes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[151,1436,1685,1999]" box="[199,732,1866,1891]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1866,1891]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,402,1866,1891]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="140.[151,250,1473,1495]" captionTargetBox="[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@140.[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 87. Hymedesmia (Stylopus) alcoladoi sp. nov., holotype RMNH Por. 9956, a, SEM image of choanosomal skeleton, b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, large acanthostyle, b 1, detail of b, c, small acanthostyle, d, tornote, d 1, details of d." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273038/files/figure.png" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Figs 87</figureCitation>
b–d) Acanthostyles, tornotes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[151,1436,1685,1999]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
Acanthostyles, in two size categories, both with heavily spined heads, (1) larger (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1212,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="140.[151,250,1473,1495]" captionTargetBox="[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@140.[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 87. Hymedesmia (Stylopus) alcoladoi sp. nov., holotype RMNH Por. 9956, a, SEM image of choanosomal skeleton, b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, large acanthostyle, b 1, detail of b, c, small acanthostyle, d, tornote, d 1, details of d." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273038/files/figure.png" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Figs 87</figureCitation>
b,b1) with spination gradually diminishing towards the pointed end, 135– 
<emphasis box="[751,793,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">176</emphasis>
–213 
<date box="[858,894,1938,1962]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">x 9</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[908,957,1938,1962]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">12.2</emphasis>
–17 µm, and (2) smaller (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1334,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="140.[151,250,1473,1495]" captionTargetBox="[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@140.[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 87. Hymedesmia (Stylopus) alcoladoi sp. nov., holotype RMNH Por. 9956, a, SEM image of choanosomal skeleton, b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, large acanthostyle, b 1, detail of b, c, small acanthostyle, d, tornote, d 1, details of d." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273038/files/figure.png" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
c) spined heavily all over, not infrequently provided with bifid pointed ends 62– 
<emphasis box="[939,967,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">79</emphasis>
–121 x 6.5– 
<emphasis box="[1100,1135,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">7.2</emphasis>
–9 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="140.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
Tornotes (
<figureCitation box="[312,401,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="140.[151,250,1473,1495]" captionTargetBox="[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@140.[155,1440,623,1455]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 87. Hymedesmia (Stylopus) alcoladoi sp. nov., holotype RMNH Por. 9956, a, SEM image of choanosomal skeleton, b – d, SEM images of spicules, b, large acanthostyle, b 1, detail of b, c, small acanthostyle, d, tornote, d 1, details of d." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273038/files/figure.png" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Figs 87</figureCitation>
d,d1), smooth, mucronate, slightly swollen pointed apices, almost symmetrical, but one end slightly thinner than the opposite end, 151– 
<emphasis box="[637,679,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">179</emphasis>
–222 
<date box="[742,776,188,212]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">x 2</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[791,826,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">2.4</emphasis>
–4 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,939,223,248]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="140.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,939,223,248]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,498,223,248]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[505,592,224,248]" name="Guyana" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Guyana</collectingCountry>
Shelf, on shells at 
<quantity box="[806,862,223,248]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" unit="m" value="64.0">64 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="140.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,260,285]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Dr. Pedro M. Alcolado (Instituto de Oceanología, 
<collectingRegion box="[1067,1155,261,284]" country="Cuba" name="La Habana" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Havana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1169,1230,260,285]" name="Cuba" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Cuba</collectingCountry>
) in recognition of his lifelong dedication to ecology and taxonomy of the Cuban sponge fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="140.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726501" collectingDate="1921-10" collectingDateMax="2010-10" collectingDateMin="1921-10" county="Theoretically" location="Moreover" municipality="However" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="No">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[321,355,333,356]" country="Haiti" name="Nord" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">No</collectingRegion>
previous records of 
<taxonomicName authority="StylOpus" authorityName="StylOpus" box="[583,846,332,357]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Hymedesmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="140" pageNumber="6" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[583,846,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Hymedesmia (Stylopus)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from the 
<collectingRegion box="[1077,1221,332,357]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Central West</collectingRegion>
Atlantic. Recently, a 
<taxonomicName box="[176,271,367,392]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Phorbas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[176,271,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Phorbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species without chelae was described, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rutzler, Piantoni, Van Soest &amp; Diaz, 2014" authorityName="Rutzler, Piantoni, Van Soest &amp; Diaz" authorityYear="2014" box="[743,1433,367,392]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Phorbas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis box="[743,910,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">P. aurantiacus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler" box="[922,1433,367,392]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" refString="Rutzler, K., Piantoni, C., Van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Diaz, M. C. (2014) Diversity of sponges (Porifera) from cryptic habitats on the Belize barrier reef near Carrie Bow Cay. Zootaxa, 3805 (1), 1 - 129. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3805.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Rützler, Piantoni, Van Soest &amp; Díaz, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCounty box="[151,302,404,429]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Theoretically</collectingCounty>
, this could be considered close or conspecific as a more mature form of the present species. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1328,1432,405,428]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">However</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,314,441,464]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Phorbas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis box="[151,314,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">P. aurantiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly different in possessing styliform tornotes and three separate categories of acanthostyles. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A8001077DCFF20FF14A5409163FDA7:8EDEE7DD77DBFF20FF14A2B6917AFE6E" box="[151,263,477,500]" county="Theoretically" municipality="However" name="Moreover" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" stateProvince="No">Moreover</location>
, both tornotes and acanthostyles reach much higher lengths (tornotes up to 590 
<date box="[1251,1307,476,500]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" value="2010-10">
<collectingDate box="[1251,1307,476,500]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" value="2010-10">x 10</collectingDate>
</date>
µm, large acanthostyles up to 410 
<date box="[440,494,512,536]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" value="1921-10">
<collectingDate box="[440,494,512,536]" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" value="1921-10">x 21</collectingDate>
</date>
µm) than in the present material. This makes it quite unlikely that the two are conspecific.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
